  <section class="intro">
  <p>This page provides quick access to edit all site content directly in GitHub.</p>

  <p>
    Content is organized by the site’s pages, with each page having a French and English version. 
    Depending on the page, the content is stored in either 
    <strong>Markdown (.md)</strong> or <strong>JSON (.json)</strong> files.
  </p>

  <p>
    To make edits, click the link for the desired file. You must be logged into GitHub with write access. 
    After committing changes, the site will redeploy automatically.
  </p>

  <p>
    For further detailed instructions, see the 
    <a href="https://github.com/MNicol1/capucine-et-tournesol/blob/main/CONTENT_EDIT_GUIDE.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Content Editing Guide</a>.
  </p>
  <div class="quick-tips">
    <h3>Quick Tips</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>When editing <strong>JSON</strong> files, always keep commas, quotes, and brackets intact.</li>
      <li>In <strong>Markdown</strong> files, leave a blank line between paragraphs and headings.</li>
      <li>Always <strong>preview</strong> your changes in GitHub before committing.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  </section>

